package com.example.cs213_tuition_project_javafx
  • Class
    Description
    Date
    Implements our date object as a comparable object.
    Enrollment
    Class to implement Enrollment object Holds an array of EnrollStudent data type, size of the array Contains methods to add, remove, print, getStudent , and check if a student is contained in the array
    EnrollStudent
    Class to implement EnrollStudent object Holds profile and creditsEnrolled as parameters Contains methods to fetch information about enrolled students' credits and change credits Contains override methods toString, equals
    International
    Class to implement International subclass which extends to its parent class NonResident Contains instance variable isStudyAbroad which will be used in tuition calculation purposes Contains override methods such as toString, isValid, and getType
    Major
    Major objects that hold major codes and the corresponding school @ Rutgers.
    NonResident
    Implementation of subclass NonResident that extends to Student superclass Contains override methods such as toString Contains methods to calculate tuition, type of nonresident student, checking to see whether or not student is a resident
    Profile
    Class to implement Profile Object.
    Resident
    Implementation of the subclass Resident that extends superclass Student Contains override methods toString, getType, isResident, tuitionDue
    Roster
    Roster Data Structure that holds Student Objects.
    Student
    Implementation of abstract class Student Contains profile, major , and creditCompleted as parameters Contains abstract methods tuitionDue and isResident Contains methods overrided methods such as toString, equals, compareTo Contains methods to check student standing, if the student is valid, and getter methods
    TriState
    Implementation of subclass TriState which extends to parent class NonResident Contains instance variable state Contains overrided methods such as toString
    TuitionManagerController
    Bridge class between JavaFX GUI and backend Java files.
    TuitionManagerMain
    Driver class for JavaFX GUI launches the JavaFX application
